<br>
I have many friends in Amnesty, and it pains me greatly to leave them.<br>
<br>
I have been in Amnesty a long time now, and have weathered many a storm with all of you.<br>
<br>
Currently, neither Amnesty nor the SGA is progressing in a direction as I would have hoped it would.  Several memebers of Amnesty have done things that I find offensive, yet their actions have not been dealt with.  <br>
<br>
Although the SGA has progressed well these last few months, it's being steered into a path that conflicts with my beliefs and goals.  <br>
<br>
I wish you all good luck.  If you need any assistance, as always feel free to look me up. <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 56 Knight<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelektraii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elektraII</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.swbell.net/mosleyrs/hobdance.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 8:05:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please accept my resignation</span><hr size=1> Saddened to see you leave mate.  Don't be a stranger! <p>Elektra
53rd Cavalier of the <a href="http://www.spiritguardians.de">Spirit Guardians</a>, Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubayen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bayen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 9:11:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hareq's Leaving</span><hr size=1> NOOOOO ! ! ! when did this happen ? ? ?  man that really blows hareq . . . i am deaply saddened that you are leaving, keep me in mind if you want to chat bro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uswmaestrosheerwill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swmaestro Sheerwill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 9:28:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please accept my resignation</span><hr size=1> Ack! Hareq, if any of your resentment was caused by me, I urge you to contact me in game.<br>
<br>
Really sorry to see you go, you have taught me alot about this game and the people in it. <p><img src="http://members.home.net/lawrenck/sig.jpg">

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyriahwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myriahwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 9:57:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please accept my resignation</span><hr size=1> Hareq, I am deeply sorry that you are leaving us. We all look up to you. We all admire you. Niema and I were just talking the other day about being embarassed because of times we were on your raids and screwed up in front of you. I remember the HUGE error I made on a FG raid and got most everyone killed. Geez I didnt want to screw up again, I can tell you.<br>
<br>
I have read your posts and believe I understand some of your reasons for leaving. As I interpret it you would like a more open raid policy, more guilds invited to share our strength, and more people leading raids. Unfortunately we dont all share the same vision. Some like all SGA raids and are committed to help those in SGA way before others. My opinion lies somewhere in between this two. Everyone has the right to their own opinion and the responsibility to voice it. I wish you could have found a way to change things in SGA more to your liking. I am sorry if, as an officer of SG and a member of SGA, I failed you again like on that FG raid.<br>
<br>
Please reconsider leaving! Maybe post your views again and let us talk about them for a few more weeks.<br>
<br>
Myriah<br>
<br>
P.S. I still owe you 300pp or a Velium Blue Diamond bracer, I will not forget!<br>
<br>
P.S.S. Come to HHH4, sat 12th at 1pm EST,and bring a friend. It is a blast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhareq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hareq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 10:12:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please accept my resignation</span><hr size=1> Swmaestro - my leaving had nothing to do with the loot policy discussion that we were engaged in.<br>
<br>
Myriah - you are correct in a lot of your assumptions, and I wish that more felt the way that I do.  As for the FG raid, we all make mistakes, and we all learn from them.  You and Niema are two of the best enchanters that I've ever had the pleasure to work with on raids, and I hope to group with both of you in the future. <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 56 Knight<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uswmaestrosheerwill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swmaestro Sheerwill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/8/01 10:17:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please accept my resignation</span><hr size=1> &quot;Several memebers of Amnesty have done things that I find offensive, yet their actions have not been dealt with.&quot;<br>
<br>
Heh after thinking about that comment I'm fairly sure I am one of the people... I can't remember (although I haven't took the time to think about it much) anyone getting pissed off at anyone else in guild without me being involved, not counting the members that were booted...<br>
